+# Phase 0287-r7-r2-r3 — Copilot v2 producer test migration
+
+## Status
+
+Corrective sub-revision for the uncommitted `0287-r7-r2` working tree.
+
+## Failure reproduced
+
+The rules suite was green, but the complete suite retained three executable
+producer tests that still supplied the historical v1 response shape. The active
+producer correctly rejected those responses and therefore wrote no advisory
+artifact.
+
+## Decision
+
+Do not infer the new objective, expected result, constraints or success criteria
+from `summary`, `suggested_route`, assumptions, questions, risks or confidence.
+That conversion would silently reinterpret the historical v1 response.
+
+Instead:
+
+- retain the existing pure v1 extraction tests for historical artifact reading;
+- migrate only tests that execute the active producer to the four-field v2
+  response contract;
+- keep the dual-artifact manifest filename and correlation contract unchanged.
+
+## Reuse audit
+
+Reused without code changes:
+
+- `run_autodoc_copilot_advisory.py`;
+- `build_autodoc_authoritative_request.py`;
+- `build_autodoc_dual_manifest.py`;
+- the existing v1 extraction helper;
+- the existing optional/fail-closed execution boundaries.
+
+No Scheduler, laboratory, SQL, Qdrant, OpenVINO, EventBus, ProjectV2 mutation or
+new adapter is introduced.
+
+## Validation target
+
+The corrected suite must prove:
+
+1. optional producer execution accepts a v2 first opinion;
+2. JSONL extraction drives a v2 artifact;
+3. the three-artifact workflow accepts the v2 advisory;
+4. historical v1 extraction tests remain present;
+5. no v1-to-v2 semantic conversion is added to production code.
+
+code_rule_review: done
+code_rule_update_required: false
+live_path_status: transition
+
+The cumulative `newicody/projects` installation guide is not changed because
+this correction alters tests only and introduces no deployment step.
